clear: right; margin-bottom: .5em; float: right; padding: .5em 0 .8em 1.4em; background: none; width: auto;"> <div id="toc" class="toc"> <div class="toctitle"> <h2>Contents</h2> </div> <ul> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#Most_common_meanings"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Most common meanings</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="#Arts,_entertainment,_and_media"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Arts, entertainment, and media</span></a> <ul> <li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-3"><a href="#Card_games"><span class="tocnumber">2.1</span> <span class="toctext">Card games</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-4"><a href="#Films"><span class="tocnumber">2.2</span> <span class="toctext">Films</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-5"><a href="#Music"><span class="tocnumber">2.3</span> <span class="toctext">Music</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-6"><a href="#Other_arts,_entertainment,_and_media"><span class="tocnumber">2.4</span> <span class="toctext">Other arts, entertainment, and media</span></a></li> </ul> </li> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-7"><a href="#Other_uses"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">Other uses</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-8"><a href="#See_also"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">See also</span></a></li> </ul> </div> </div> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Most_common_meanings">Most common meanings</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Most common meanings">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(ability)" title="Balance (ability)">Balance (ability)</a> in biomechanics</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(accounting)" title="Balance (accounting)">Balance (accounting)</a></li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(device_for_weighing)" class="mw-redirect" title="Balance (device for weighing)">Balance (device for weighing)</a> or weighing scale</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Equilibrioception" class="mw-redirect" title="Equilibrioception">Equilibrioception</a>, the physiological sense of balance</li> </ul> <h2><span id="Arts.2C_entertainment.2C_and_media"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Arts,_entertainment,_and_media">Arts, entertainment, and media</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Arts, entertainment, and media">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Card_games">Card games</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Card games">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <ul> <li>Several distinct meanings in the game of contract bridge, including: <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Balanced_hand" title="Balanced hand">Balanced hand</a></li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balancing_(bridge)" title="Balancing (bridge)">Balancing (bridge)</a></li> </ul> </li> </ul> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Films">Films</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Films">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(1983_film)" title="Balance (1983 film)"><i>Balance</i> (1983 film)</a>, a Bulgarian film</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(1989_film)" title="Balance (1989 film)"><i>Balance</i> (1989 film)</a>, a short animated film</li> <li><i><a href="/wiki/La_Balance" title="La Balance">La Balance</a></i>, a 1982 French film</li> </ul> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Music">Music</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Music">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(band)" title="Balance (band)">Balance (band)</a>, a 1980s pop-rock group</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(Van_Halen_album)" title="Balance (Van Halen album)"><i>Balance</i> (Van Halen album)</a>, 1995</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(Kim-Lian_album)" title="Balance (Kim-Lian album)"><i>Balance</i> (Kim-Lian album)</a>, 2004</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(Akrobatik_album)" title="Balance (Akrobatik album)"><i>Balance</i> (Akrobatik album)</a>, 2003</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(Leo_Kottke_album)" title="Balance (Leo Kottke album)"><i>Balance</i> (Leo Kottke album)</a>, 1978</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(Swollen_Members_album)" title="Balance (Swollen Members album)"><i>Balance</i> (Swollen Members album)</a>, 1999</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(Ty_Tabor_album)" title="Balance (Ty Tabor album)"><i>Balance</i> (Ty Tabor album)</a>, 2008</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(Joe_Morris_album)" title="Balance (Joe Morris album)"><i>Balance</i> (Joe Morris album)</a>, 2014</li> <li>"<a href="/wiki/The_Balance" class="mw-redirect" title="The Balance">The Balance</a>", a Moody Blues song on the 1970 album <i>A Question of Balance</i></li> <li>"Balance", a song by Axium from <i><a href="/wiki/The_Story_Thus_Far_(album)" class="mw-redirect" title="The Story Thus Far (album)">The Story Thus Far</a></i></li> </ul> <h3><span id="Other_arts.2C_entertainment.2C_and_media"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Other_arts,_entertainment,_and_media">Other arts, entertainment, and media</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Other arts, entertainment, and media">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(advertisement)" title="Balance (advertisement)">Balance (advertisement)</a>, a 1989 award-winning television advertisement for the Lexus LS 400</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(game_design)" title="Balance (game design)">Balance (game design)</a>, the concept and the practice of tuning relationships between a game's component systems</li> <li>"Balance", a poem by Patti Smith from the book <i><a href="/wiki/Kodak_(book)" title="Kodak (book)">kodak</a></i></li> <li>"Balancing", an <a href="/wiki/List_of_Teletubbies_episodes_and_videos" title="List of Teletubbies episodes and videos">episode of the television series <i>Teletubbies</i></a></li> <li><i><a href="/wiki/Balance:_Television_for_Living_Well" title="Balance: Television for Living Well">Balance: Television for Living Well</a></i>, a Canadian television talk show</li> </ul> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Other_uses">Other uses</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Other uses">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(metaphysics)" title="Balance (metaphysics)">Balance (metaphysics)</a>, a desirable point between two or more opposite forces</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_(puzzle)" title="Balance (puzzle)">Balance (puzzle)</a>, a mathematical puzzle</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balance_wheel" title="Balance wheel">Balance wheel</a>, the timing device in mechanical watches</li> <li>Balanced, one of the <a href="/wiki/Wine_tasting_descriptors" title="Wine tasting descriptors">wine tasting descriptors</a></li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balancing_(international_relations)" title="Balancing (international relations)">Balancing (international relations)</a></li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balancing_and_deranking" title="Balancing and deranking">Balancing and deranking</a>, in grammar the use in subordinate clauses of verb forms identical to those in main clauses</li> </ul> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: See also">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/BALANCE_Act" title="BALANCE Act">BALANCE Act</a> (Benefit Authors without Limiting Advancement or Net Consumer Expectations Act), proposed US federal legislation</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Balancing_machine" title="Balancing machine">Balancing machine</a>, a measuring tool used for balancing rotating machine parts</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Load_balancing_(computing)" title="Load balancing (computing)">Load balancing (computing)</a>, <a href="/wiki/Computer_network" title="Computer network">computer networking</a> method for distributing workloads across multiple computing resources</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Tire_balance" title="Tire balance">Tire balance</a>, the distribution of mass within an automobile tire or the entire wheel to which it is attached</li> </ul> <table id="disambigbox" class="metadata plainlinks dmbox dmbox-disambig" style="" role="presentation"> <tr> <td class="mbox-image" style="padding: 2px 0 2px 0.4em;"><a href="/wiki/File:Disambig_gray.svg" class="image"><img alt="Disambiguation icon" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/5f/Disambig_gray.svg/30px-Disambig_gray.svg.png" width="30" height="23" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/5f/Disambig_gray.svg/45px-Disambig_gray.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/5f/Disambig_gray.svg/60px-Disambig_gray.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="220" data-file-height="168" /></a></td> <td class="mbox-text" style="padding: 0.25em 0.4em; font-style: italic;">This <a href="/wiki/Help:Disambiguation" title="Help:Disambiguation">disambiguation</a> page lists articles associated with th